quran[78]{c,v,t}:
  55,1,The All-Merciful
  55,2,taught the Qur´an
  55,3,He created man
  55,4,and taught him clear expression
  55,5,The sun and the moon both run with precision
  55,6,The shrubs and the trees all bow down in prostration
  55,7,He erected heaven and established the balance
  55,8,so that you would not transgress the balance
  55,9,Give just weight — do not skimp in the balance
  55,10,He laid out the earth for all living creatures
  55,11,In it are fruits and date-palms with covered spathes
  55,12,and grains on leafy stems and fragrant herbs
  55,13,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,14,He created man from dry earth like baked clay
  55,15,and He created the jinn from a fusion of fire
  55,16,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,17,The Lord of the two Easts and the Lord of the two Wests
  55,18,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,19,"He has let loose the two seas, converging together"
  55,20,with a barrier between them they do not break through
  55,21,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,22,From out of them come glistening pearls and coral
  55,23,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,24,"His, too, are the ships sailing like mountain peaks on the sea"
  55,25,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,26,Everyone on it will pass away
  55,27,"but the Face of your Lord will remain, Master of Majesty and Generosity"
  55,28,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,29,Everyone in the heavens and earth requests His aid. Every day He is engaged in some affair
  55,30,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,31,"Soon We will settle your affairs, you two weighty throngs"
  55,32,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,33,"Company of jinn and men, if you are able to pierce through the confines of the heavens and earth, pierce through them. You will not pierce through except with a clear authority"
  55,34,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,35,"He will pursue you with a piercing flame and fiery smoke, and you will not be helped"
  55,36,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,37,When heaven is split apart and goes red like dregs of oil
  55,38,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,39,That Day no man or jinn will be asked about his sin
  55,40,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,41,The evildoers will be recognised by their mark and seized by their forelocks and their feet
  55,42,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,43,This is Hell which the evildoers deny
  55,44,They will go back and forth between fire and scalding water
  55,45,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,46,For those who fear the Station of their Lord there are two Gardens
  55,47,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,48,Shaded by spreading branches
  55,49,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,50,In them are two clear flowing springs
  55,51,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,52,In them are two kinds of every fruit
  55,53,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,54,"They will be reclining on couches lined with rich brocade, the fruits of the Gardens hanging close to hand"
  55,55,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,56,"In them are maidens with eyes for them alone, untouched before them by either man or jinn"
  55,57,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,58,Like precious gems of ruby and pearl
  55,59,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,60,Will the reward for doing good be anything other than good
  55,61,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,62,As well as those two there will be two other Gardens
  55,63,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,64,Of deep viridian green
  55,65,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,66,In them are two gushing springs
  55,67,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,68,In them are fruits and date-palms and pomegranates
  55,69,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,70,"In them are sweet, lovely maidens"
  55,71,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,72,"Dark-eyed, secluded in cool pavilions"
  55,73,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,74,Untouched before them by either man or jinn
  55,75,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,76,Reclining on green quilts and exquisite rugs
  55,77,So which of your Lord´s blessings do you both then deny
  55,78,"Blessed be the name of your Lord, Master of Majesty and Generosity"